England  and  Italy  were tied 0-0 at
the end of the first period of extra time in their quarterfinal
in Kiev, Ukraine at soccerâ€™s European Championship.  If the teams remain tied, the match will be decided by a
penalty shootout. Italy has had about three times more shots on
goal and over 60 percent possession during the match so far.  The winner of the match at the Olympic Stadium will play
record three-time champion Germany in the semifinals. The other
semifinal will be between defending champion Spain and Portugal.  England, which last reached the semifinals in 1996, is
looking to win the tournament for a first time. Italy is the
1968 champion.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
